      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum mechanics formulation with nonlinear geometry (large deformation) and frictional contact at screw-rod interface justified and documented.",
      "rationale": "The model employs a nonlinear continuum mechanics formulation with large-deformation kinematics and penalty-based frictional contact (mu=0.2) at the screw-rod interface. This form is consistent with published literature on spinal implant FEA and captures the dominant load-transfer mechanisms under ASTM F1717 compression-bending."
