      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories using production-representative 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screws from the same manufacturing lot. Sample size exceeds the N=5 minimum and provides adequate statistical basis for mean and variability comparison."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span clinically relevant load configurations; at minimum two load levels or orientations evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed exclusively under the standard ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration at a single load offset. No variation in load angle or offset distance was explored. This limits generalizability and results in an achieved level below the required level for this factor. Accepted overall because remaining factors collectively satisfy the credibility threshold for Medium model risk."
    },
    {
