    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The overall credibility assessment is Accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged; however, the remaining factor evidence collectively demonstrates sufficient model credibility for the intended Medium model risk, Medium consequence application. All quantitative acceptance criteria for output comparison are satisfied (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10% for all QoIs). The assessment team judges the residual uncertainty associated with the single-condition test protocol to be acceptable given the direct applicability of the ASTM F1717 standardized test to the COU.",
